    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\n`nargs = \"1\"` is not supported, neovim throws an error.\n\nhttps://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/34210 added support for `nargs`, but didn't include `nargs = \"1\"` in the tests (and sure enough, it doesn't work).\n\nThis is not a blocker, as `command-nargs` of values `*`, `+`, `?` can cover the need, but having all documented `command-nargs` values supported except for `\"1\"` is confusing.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nCreate user command and source it\n\n```lua\nvim.api.nvim_create_user_command(\"MyCommand\", function(args)\n\tvim.notify(vim.inspect(args))\nend, { nargs = \"1\" })\n```\n\nResults in: `Invalid 'nargs': '1'`.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nEither:\n- `nargs = \"1\"` should be a valid argument as per `:h command-nargs`.\n- Document `:h nvim_create_user_command()`, `nargs` section, saying \"1\" is not supported and why. \n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\n0.13-beta\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nLinux\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nGhostty 1.3.1-arch1.1\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-ghostty\n\n### Installation\n\nbuild from repo",
