    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "I think `nargs = \"1\"` (and `\"0\"`) should be supported as valid string values. The API already accepts `\"*\"`, `\"?\"`, and `\"+\"` as strings, so i believe rejecting `\"0\"` and `\"1\"` is inconsistent\n\n```bash\n// :h command-nargs\nArgument handling ~ *E175* *E176* *:command-nargs*\n........\n\t-nargs=0    No arguments are allowed (the default)\n\t-nargs=1    Exactly one argument is required, it includes spaces\n\t-nargs=*    Any number of arguments are allowed (0, 1, or many),\n\t\t    separated by white space\n\t-nargs=?    0 or 1 arguments are allowed\n\t-nargs=+    Arguments must be supplied, but any number are allowed\n```\n\nI can open a PR for this.",
